%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Martha's%20Vineyard%20Airport%20sign.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c897b7a3c8094d5dd8d93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221296%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMartha's%20Vineyard%20Airport.%3Cp%3ENancy%20Lane%2FMediaNews%20Group%2FBoston%20Herald%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMassachusetts'%20new%20tax%20on%20the%20wealthy%20generated%20%241.8%20billion%2C%20exceeding%20expectations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EApproved%20in%202022%2C%20the%20tax%20added%204%25%20on%20incomes%20over%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20increased%20revenue%20comes%20amid%20high-income%20earners%20leaving%20the%20state.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMassachusetts'%20new%20tax%20on%20the%20wealthy%20has%20become%20a%20bigger%20boon%20for%20the%20state%20than%20expected.%20It%20could%20help%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emake%20up%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20high-income%20earners%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20announced%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20tax%20brought%20in%20%241.8%20billion%20in%20the%20first%20three%20quarters%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%2C%20blowing%20away%20predictions%20for%20the%20entire%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2024%2F05%2F20%2Fmetro%2Fmillionaires-tax-massachusetts-generated-18-billion%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DState%2520officials%2520said%2520Monday%2520that%2Con%2520transportation%2520and%2520education%2520initiatives.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Boston%20Globe.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20additional%20income%20for%20the%20state%20is%20already%20%24800%20million%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emore%20than%20what%20lawmakers%20had%20budgeted%20to%20spend%20from%20the%20new%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20tax%20on%20the%20wealthy%2C%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3Bmillionaires%20tax%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20approved%20by%20voters%20in%202022%20and%20added%20an%20additional%204%25%20tax%20on%20those%20earning%20more%20than%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2023%2F01%2F24%2Fmetro%2Fnew-millionaires-tax-could-generate-least-14-billion-next-year-state-officials-project%2F%3Fp1%3DArticle_Inline_Text_Link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Boston%20Globe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20the%20tax%20was%20approved%2C%20the%20state%20initially%20estimated%20it%20would%20generate%20%241.4%20to%20%241.7%20billion%20in%20the%20first%20year.%20However%2C%20the%20state%20budgeted%20just%20%241%20billion%20for%20the%20first%20year%20out%20of%20concerns%20that%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20new%20tax%20could%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FRM6MR%23selection-1917.0-1917.28%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunreliable%20in%20the%20first%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20windfall%20for%20the%20state%20comes%20despite%20concerns%20that%20high-income%20earners%20would%20leave%20the%20state%2C%20exacerbating%20a%20problem%20seen%20in%20Massachusetts%20even%20before%20the%20new%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpioneerinstitute.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FPNR-521-TaxReality-PB-v03.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20study%20by%20the%20Pioneer%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202023%20showed%20that%20Massachusetts%20saw%20a%20net%20loss%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E25%2C200%20tax%20filers%20in%202021.%20Those%20who%20left%20the%20state%20had%20an%20adjusted%20gross%20income%20of%20%244.3%20billion%20greater%20than%20those%20who%20moved%20in.%20The%20change%20in%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20filers%20increased%20from%20the%20net%20loss%20of%2020%2C400%20tax%20filers%20in%202020%20and%20an%20adjusted%20gross%20income%20of%20%242.4%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20left%20tended%20to%20be%20middle-%20to%20high-income%20earners%2C%20per%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonin