20ranks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-americans-earning-above-poverty-live-paycheck-to-paycheck-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EALICE%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20They're%20asset-limited%2C%20income-constrained%2C%20but%20employed.%20In%20practical%20terms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-typical-alice-middle-class-poverty-housing-food-benefits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20a%20third%20of%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20working%20and%20making%20enough%20money%20not%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20public%20assistance%20but%20are%20still%20struggling%20to%20get%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20data%20from%20research%20organization%20United%20For%20ALICE%2C%20shared%20exclusively%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20looks%20at%20the%20ALICE%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unitedforalice.org%2Fwage-tool%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousehold%20survival%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20varies%20county%20by%20county%20and%20measures%20how%20much%20a%20family%20needs%20to%20make%20to%20afford%20necessities.%20The%20survival%20budget%20considers%20expenses%20such%20as%20food%2C%20housing%2C%20childcare%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20healthcare%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20taxes%20and%20an%20emergency%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20ALICE%20household%20survival%20budgets%20for%20a%20typical%20family%20of%20four%20look%20like%20across%20the%20country.%20These%20budgets%20are%20the%20highest%20in%20coastal%20states%2C%20and%20some%20budgets%20are%20well%20into%20six%20figures.%20Some%20states%2C%20such%20as%20California%20and%20Virginia%2C%20are%20entirely%20dark%20blue%2C%20meaning%20budgets%20of%20over%20%2485%2C000%20in%20each%20county%2C%20while%20others%20are%20almost%20entirely%20lighter%20blue%2C%20where%20budgets%20are%20in%20the%20%2460%2C000s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3