20larger%20county%20with%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20%E2%80%94%20that%20budget%20is%20%2468%2C784.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20report%2C%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20the%20number%20of%20ALICE%20households%20rose%20by%20nearly%201.6%20million%2C%20while%20the%20number%20of%20households%20in%20poverty%20increased%20by%20208%2C000.%20The%20total%20number%20of%20ALICE%20households%20jumped%2012%25%20between%202010%20and%202022%2C%20particularly%20impacting%20single%20parents%20and%20people%20of%20color.%20During%20these%2012%20years%2C%20the%20percent%20change%20in%20single-male-headed%20ALICE%20households%20grew%2035%25.%20As%20many%20as%2054%20million%20American%20families%2C%20or%2042%25%2C%20are%20below%20the%20ALICE%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildcare%20costs%20have%20also%20skyrocketed%20recently.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20the%20cost%20to%20care%20for%20one%20child%20this%20year%20is%20at%20least%20%2425%2C714.%20According%20to%20United%20Way%2C%20over%20a%20third%20of%20parents%20said%20they%20cut%20work%20hours%20or%20took%20unpaid%20leave%20when%20childcare%20facilities%20were%20unaffordable%20or%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20wages%20have%20increased%20across%20the%20board%20for%20many%20lower-wage%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20cases%20faster%20than%20inflation.%20From%202019%20to%202022%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20wages%20for%20cashiers%20grew%2019%25%2C%20for%20fast%20food%20and%20counter%20workers%2023%25%2C%20and%20for%20waiters%2027%25.%20However%2C%20it's%20becoming%20increasingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-adding-low-paying-healthcare-retail-jobs-high-wages-scarce-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20find%20higher-payin