state%20types%20I%20encountered%20while%20reporting%20on%20the%20city's%20housing%20market%20were%20fond%20of%20the%20nicknames%2C%20too.%20Soon%20I%20was%20parroting%20them%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20relocated%20to%20an%20up-and-coming%20American%20city%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20you've%20likely%20had%20to%20decipher%20a%20similar%20code.%20Developers%20and%20business%20associations%20have%20long%20slapped%20pithy%20names%20on%20fast-growing%20parts%20of%20town%2C%20and%20tenured%20residents%20have%20long%20rolled%20their%20eyes%20at%20them.%20But%20with%20the%20growing%20adoption%20of%20these%20new%20abbreviations%2C%20I%20think%20I'm%20ready%20to%20say%20enough%20is%20enough.%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20has%20MoRA%20and%20LoSo%3B%20Nashville's%20got%20SoBro%3B%20Boston%20has%20SoWa.%20In%20Louisville%2C%20Kentucky%20(which%20also%20has%20a%20SoBro)%2C%20you%20may%20find%20yourself%20sipping%20a%20craft%20beer%20in%20NuLu.%20My%20hometown%20of%20Austin%20already%20has%20SoCo%2C%20and%20the%20powers%20that%20be%20are%20trying%20to%20make%20%26quot%3BSoLa%26quot%3B%20happen.%20The%20path%20of%20progress%20is%20paved%20with%20nonsense%20nomenclature%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20my%20editor%20calls%20them%2C%20%26quot%3B'Sound%20of%20Music'-ass%20names.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20unholy%20mashups%20would%20be%20fine%2C%20I%20guess%2C%20if%20they%20were%20dumb%20yet%20harmless%20inventions.%20But%20they're%20not%20just%20silly%20nicknames%20or%20low-lift%20marketing%20ploys.%20They're%20the%20calling%20cards%20of%20developers%20and%20new%20arrivals%20as%20they%20try%20to%20wipe%20the%20slate%20clean%20on%20existing%20neighborhoods%20and%20remake%20them%20in%20their%20image.%20I'm%20all%20for%20building%20more%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-inequality-housing-shortage-causes-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20way%20out%20of%20our%20affordability%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20all.%20If%20a%20goofy%20new%20name%20is%20all%20that's%20needed%20to%20convince%20well-off%20transplants%20to%20flock%20to%20glass%20towers%20in%20a%20once%20deserted%20part%20of%20town%2C%20then%20great!%20But%20often%20it's%20more%20about%20renaming%20a%20place%20where%20people%20already%20live%20in%20hopes%20that%20whitewashing%20its%20history%20will%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20attract%20wealthy%20people%20and%20drive%20up%20the%20property%20values%20%E2%80%94%20inevitably%20sending%20longtime%20residents%20packing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worry%20that%20the%20pandemic%20reshuffling%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-home-house-prices-rent-cost-decline-cheaper-cities-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escattered%20white-collar%20workers%20across%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20search%20of%20wide%20open%20spaces%2C%20will%20only%20encourage%20more%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20behavior.%20As%20cities%20bend%20over%20backward%20to%20attract%20a%20certain%20type%20of%20middle-%20and%20high-income%20worker%2C%20they%20often%20end%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-american-cities-look-the-same-remote-work-city-authentic-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooking%20the%20same%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%20they're%20sounding%20the%20same%2C%20too.%20Let's%20at%20least%20call%20these%20two-syllable%20monikers%20what%20they%20are%3A%20cookie-cutter%20attempts%20to%20herd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-student-loans-six-figure-income-millennial-gen-z-retirement-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHENRYs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnet-worth-dink-child-free-couples-win-the-economy-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%20toward%20new%20coffee%20shops%20and%20studio%20apartments%20in%20areas%20they%20would%20have%20avoided%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20like%20every%20undervalued%20neighborhood%20in%20America%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20rebrand.%20But%20the%20SoBros%20and%20SoWas%20of%20the%20world%20are%20just%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20egregious%20outcomes%20of%20contentious%20battles%20over%20neighborhoods'%20names%20and%20boundaries.%20And%20unless%20we%20put%20our%20collective%20foot%20down%2C%20we're%20bound%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGill%20Holland%20moved%20from%20New%20York%20City%20to%20Louisville%20in%202005.%20Holland%2C%20a%20serial%20entrepreneur%20and%20real-estate%20developer%2C%20is%20a%20country%20boy%20at%20heart%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20a%20small%20town%20in%20North%20Carolina%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20yearned%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20vibrant%2C%20walkable%20streets%20he'd%20come%20to%20love%20as%20a%20resident%20of%20Manhattan's%20Greenwich%20Village%20neighborhood.%20He%20began%20renting%20office%20space%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20Louisville's%20downtown%2C%20in%20a%20run-down%20area%20that%20was%20home%20to%2C%20in%20his%20words%2C%20%26quot%3Blots%20of%20great%2C%20old%20buildings.%26quot%3B%20Holland%20saw%20potential.%20But%20there%20was%20another%20issue.%20All%20the%20surrounding%20areas%20had%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20brands%26quot%3B%3A%20strong%20names%20with%20history%20behind%20them%2C%20like%20Butchertown%2C%20Smoketown%2C%20and%20Phoenix%20Hill.%20Holland's%20chosen%20zone%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20had%20no%20such%20calling%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20kept%20thinking%2C%20like%2C%20this%20part%20of%20town%20needs%20a%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20Holland%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20local%20business%20association%20tried%20out%20%26quot%3BEast%20Market%20District%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20stuck%20for%20a%20little%20bit.%20But%20Holland%20was%20quietly%20floating%20another%20name%2C%20one%20that%20represented%20the%20%26quot%3BNew-York-to-Louisville%20bridge%26quot%3B%20he%20was%20already%20building%20in%20his%20mind.%20When%20he%20opened%20an%20art%20gallery%20in%20the%20area%2C%20he%20lopped%20off%20the%20first%20syllable%20of%20each%20city%20and%20stitched%20them%20together.%20The%20result%20was%20NuLu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20cities%20have%20processes%20for%20naming%20neighborhoods%20and%20defining%20their%20limits%2C%20most%20often%20things%20are%20more%20informal.%20Neighborhood%20names%2C%20as%20the%20law%20professors%20Nestor%20Davidson%20and%20David%20Fagundes%20noted%20in%20a%202019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarship.law.vanderbilt.edu%2Fvlr%2Fvol72%2Fiss3%2F1%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20long%20been%20a%20neat%20little%20trick%20of%20advertising%20devised%20by%20%26quot%3Breal%20estate%20agents%20and%20developers%2C%20or%20community%20groups%20like%20neighborhood%20associations.%26quot%3B%20An%20apartment%20owner%20might%20come%20up%20with%20a%20catchy%20name%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20draw%20new%20tenants%2C%20new%20arrivals%20might%20will%20a%20neighborhood%20into%20existence%20merely%20by%20saying%20it%20a%20lot%2C%20or%20some%20communities%20might%20band%20together%20to%20intentionally%20reclaim%20an%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20enterprising%20groups%20understand%20that%20neighborhood%20%26quot%3Bbrands%26quot%3B%20play%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20attracting%20new%20arrivals%20and%20helping%20them%20establish%20their%20place%20in%20a%20city%20(while%20also%20luring%20them%20to%20spend%20their%20dollars%20at%20the%20shops%2C%20art%20galleries%2C%20and%20restaurants%20in%20burgeoning%20areas).%20Neighborhood%20names%20are%20proxies%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20you%20are%20or%20hope%20to%20become.%20We%20choose%20a%20neighborhood%20that%20matches%20our%20sense%20of%20self%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20place%20where%20we%20can%20find%20%3Cem%3Eour%3C%2Fem%3E%20people.%20Or%20we%20latch%20on%20to%20a%20neighborhood%20to%20craft%20a%20new%20identity%2C%20taking%20on%20the%20qualities%20of%20the%20area%20in%20which%20we%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeighborhood%20names%20are%20also%20shorthand%20for%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-renting-buying-affordability-mortgage-rates-home-prices-rent-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erent%20or%20mortgage%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202018%20study%20from%20the%20online%20home-improvement%20platform%20Porch%20found%20that%20areas%20with%20%26quot%3BHills%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIsland%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BVillage%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BOaks%26quot%3B%20tended%20to%20have%20the%20highest%20household%20incomes%20across%20the%20US.%20Areas%20with%20the%20Spanish%20words%20%26quot%3BLos%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BLas%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20names%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20were%20among%20the%20neighborhoods%20with%20the%20lowest%20incomes.%20In%20another%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2220-9964%2F7%2F10%2F388%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20from%20McGill%20University%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%20noted%20that%20real-estate%20companies%20relied%20on%20neighborhood%20boundaries%20to%20compare%20prices%20across%20properties%20and%20that%20being%20associated%20with%20a%20desirable%20neighborhood%20could%20improve%20access%20to%20things%20like%20healthcare%20or%20lower%20mortgage%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeighborhood%20nicknames%20have%20a%20rich%20tradition%20in%20New%20York%3A%20There's%20SoHo%2C%20an%20abbreviation%20for%20South%20of%20Houston%20Street%20(which%20also%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20inspiration%20for%20the%20wave%20of%20two-syllable%20monikers%20that%20has%20followed)%2C%20Dumbo%20(Down%20Under%20the%20Manhattan%20Bridge%20Overpass)%2C%20FiDi%20(the%20Financial%20District)%2C%20and%20Tribeca%20(the%20Triangle%20Below%20Canal%20Street).%20Landlords%20in%20the%20city%20often%20try%20to%20stretch%20the%20boundaries%20of%20desirable%20neighborhoods%20when%20advertising%20their%20properties%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20rolled%20my%20eyes%20at%20listings%20that%20claimed%20to%20be%20in%20high-demand%20neighborhoods%20like%20the%20Lower%20East%20Side%20or%20Chelsea%20when%20no%20reasonable%20local%20would%20agree.%20This%20practice%20isn't%20unique%20to%20New%20York.%20The%20researchers%20from%20McGill%20and%20Maryland%20found%20that%20affluent%20or%20otherwise%20desirable%20neighborhoods%20around%20the%20country%20appeared%20to%20be%20much%20larger%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20landlords%20advertising%20their%20properties%20on%20Craigslist%20than%20they%20were%20according%20to%20less%20biased%20third%20parties%20like%20Google%20Maps%20or%20city%20planning%20departments.%20Meanwhile%2C%20landlords%20who%20advertised%20rental%20properties%20in%20areas%20with%20lower-income%2C%20nonwhite%20communities%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20include%20the%20neighborhood's%20name%20in%20their%20listings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20single%20neighborhood%20name%20invokes%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20different%20connotations%20or%20feelings%20for%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20McKenzie%2C%20a%20geography%20professor%20at%20McGill%20who%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20research%20team%2C%20told%20me.%20Landlords%20are%20all%20too%20aware%20of%20this%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20mention%20a%20neighborhood%20that%20has%20a%20negative%20connotation%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bit%20immediately%20jumps%20out%20in%20the%20listing%2C%26quot%3B%20McKenzie%20said.%20The%20solution%3F%20Spin%20up%20new%20shorthand%20to%20drum%20up%20interest%20in%20an%20old%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20where%20things%20get%20cringey.%20In%202017%2C%20real-estate%20brokers%20in%20the%20historically%20Black%20New%20York%20neighborhood%20of%20Harlem%20sparked%20backlash%20when%20they%20tried%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fr-move-to-rename-harlem-sparks-outrage-over-erasing-black-history-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erebrand%20its%20south%20end%20as%20SoHa%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Years%20earlier%2C%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%2C%20then%20a%20Democratic%20lawmaker%20in%20the%20New%20York%20State%20Assembly%2C%20had%20proposed%20legislation%20to%20ban%20neighborhood%20renaming%2C%20claiming%20the%20practice%20artificially%20inflated%20housing%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNeighborhoods%20have%20a%20history%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20character%20that%20should%20not%20be%20tossed%20overboard%20whenever%20a%20Realtor%20decides%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20to%20market%20under%20another%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffries%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20a%20new%20neighborhood%20name%20might%20signal%20it's%20already%20too%20late.%20Davidson%20told%20me%20that%20once%20a%20neighborhood%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20cachet%2C%20shortening%20its%20name%2C%20%C3%A1%20la%20SoHo%2C%20can%20be%20a%20way%20of%20formally%20announcing%20its%20arrival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20better%20or%20worse%2C%20and%20I%20think%20often%20worse%2C%20it%20is%20a%20way%20of%20signaling%20exclusion%20and%20signaling%20that%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20people%20are%20living%20in%20that%20neighborhood%2C%26quot%3B%20Davidson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20can%20have%20consequences%20for%20gentrification%20or%20displacement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SoHa%20controversy%20isn't%20unique%20to%20the%20Big%20Apple%20%E2%80%94%20in%20Denver%2C%20many%20developers%20proudly%20tout%20their%20buildings'%20locations%20in%20the%20River%20North%20Arts%20District%2C%20or%20RiNo%2C%20without%20mentioning%20that%20the%20district%20is%20a%20relatively%20new%20creation%20overlaid%20on%20part%20of%20the%20historically%20Black%20neighborhood%20of%20Five%20Points.%20The%20South%20Congress%20strip%20in%20Austin%20used%20to%20be%20home%20to%20a%20brothel%20and%20porn%20theater%3B%20today%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F14-best-austin-texas-neighborhoods-people-moving-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisit%20to%20SoCo%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20include%20a%20splurge%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhermes-gen-z-resale-birkin-bag-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHerm%C3%A8s%20store%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20stroll%20past%20the%20members-only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-soho-house-member-club-worth-fee-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoho%20House%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20developers%2C%20brokers%2C%20or%20whoever%20else%20is%20behind%20these%20rebrands%2C%20the%20abbreviations%20are%20a%20kind%20of%20compromise%2C%20McKenzie%20said.%20They're%20not%20total%20erasures%2C%20but%20they're%20clearly%20designed%20with%20a%20fresh%20start%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20attempt%20to%20adjust%20things%20without%20blatantly%20coming%20in%20and%20putting%20a%20brand-new%20name%20that%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20McKenzie%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%20shortening%20it%20to%20this%20sexy%20acronym%2C%20you're%20able%20to%20sort%20of%20mask%20a%20bit%20of%20the%20historical%20name%20that%20maybe%20has%20some%20negative%20connotation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20rationale%20behind%20some%20of%20these%20rebrands%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20argue%20with%20the%20results.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20SoCo%2C%20a%20thriving%20retail%20district%20is%20certainly%20preferable%20to%20its%20seedy%20past.%20Louisville's%20NuLu%20neighborhood%2C%20which%20eventually%20caught%20on%20among%20other%20residents%2C%20has%20received%20more%20than%20half%20a%20billion%20dollars%20in%20investment%20since%20Holland%20coined%20the%20term%20around%202006%2C%20he%20told%20me.%20Bob%20Dylan's%20whiskey%20company%20is%20opening%20a%20restaurant%2C%20bar%2C%20and%20live-music%20venue%20there.%20The%20times%20are%20indeed%20a-changin'.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENIMBY%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20need%20to%20build%20a%20lot%20more%20homes%20across%20all%20price%20points%2C%20and%20we%20need%20developers%20to%20move%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-build-infrastructure-transportation-housing-regulation-environment-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emountains%20of%20red%20tape%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20to%20make%20it%20all%20happen.%20At%20their%20best%2C%20new%20neighborhood%20names%20bring%20people%20together%20over%20a%20shared%20sense%20of%20pride%20in%20their%20little%20corner%20of%20the%20world.%20But%20at%20their%20worst%2C%20they're%20cynical%20chess%20moves%20designed%20to%20grease%20the%20wheels%20of%20gentrification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20way%2C%20these%20neighborhood%20names%20have%20veered%20into%20parody%20territory.%20In%20%26quot%3BHow%20I%20Met%20Your%20Mother%2C%26quot%3B%20Marshall%20and%20Lily%20buy%20an%20apartment%20in%20the%20fictional%20neighborhood%20of%20Dowisetrepla%20before%20realizing%20its%20name%20stands%20for%20%3Cstrong%3EDo%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewn%3Cstrong%3Ewi%3C%2Fstrong%3End%20of%20the%20%3Cstrong%3ESe%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewage%20%3Cstrong%3ETre%3C%2Fstrong%3Eatment%20%3Cstrong%3EPla%3C%2Fstrong%3Ent.%20When%20a%20%26quot%3BSouth%20Park%26quot%3B%20character%20urges%20his%20fellow%20citizens%20to%20revamp%20their%20town%2C%20the%20result%20is%20a%20new%20shopping%20district%20called%20SoDoSoPa.%20Like%20any%20good%20piece%20of%20satire%2C%20these%20names%20aren't%20too%20far%20off%20from%20their%20real-life%20inspiration.%20When%20a%20Redditor%20posts%20a%20map%20of%20Charlotte%20with%20a%20reference%20to%20WeLoSo%20(West%20of%20Lower%20South%20End)%2C%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20tell%20if%20they're%20kidding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20jokes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Scrabble-tile%20neighborhood%20names%20have%20been%20around%20for%20years%2C%20I%20think%20we're%20destined%20to%20see%20a%20groundswell%20of%20new%20targets%20as%20pandemic-era%20transplants%20settle%20into%20their%20chosen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-flooding-zoomtowns-causing-affordable-housing-crisis-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZoomtowns%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20not%20saying%20that%20neighborhood%20names%20should%20be%20set%20in%20stone%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20natural%20for%20them%20to%20evolve%20alongside%20their%20populations.%20But%20I%20think%20our%20cities%2C%20and%20their%20residents%2C%20deserve%20better%20than%20the%20lazy%20rebrands%20we've%20seen%20of%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20one%20X%20user%20wondered%20aloud%20whether%20a%20section%20of%20Brooklyn's%20East%20Williamsburg%20neighborhood%2C%20outlined%20on%20a%20map%20in%20a%20yellow%20box%2C%20was%20worthy%20of%20a%20new%20name%20given%20its%20appeal%20to%20a%20specific%20kind%20of%20tech%20professional.%20The%20post%20drew%20some%20earnest%20comments%20(%26quot%3BEast%20Willy!%26quot%3B)%20and%20plenty%20of%20backlash%20(%26quot%3Bi'm%20begging%20u%20pls%20don't%20make%20this%20a%20thing%26quot%3B).%20But%20one%20reaction%2C%20from%20the%20downtown%20gadfly%20known%20as%20Nolita%20Dirtbag%20%E2%80%94%20his%20own%20moniker%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20neighborhood%20that%20gets%20its%20name%20from%20a%20mashup%20of%20North%20of%20Little%20Italy%20%E2%80%94%20asked%20simply%20for%20a%20little%20introspection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BListen%20to%20yourself%2C%20man.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%