y%20tech%20giants%2C%20like%20Meta's%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Google's%20Sundar%20Pichai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHere%20are%20some%20facts%20about%20Nikesh%20Arora%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.iitbhufoundation.org%2Fmr-nikesh-arora-ece-89%2F%5C%22%3ENikesh%20Arora%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20born%20on%20February%209%2C%201968%2C%20in%20Ghaziabad%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20His%20father%20served%20in%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force.%20He%20studied%20at%20The%20Air%20Force%20School%20(Subroto%20Park)%20before%20graduating%20in%20Electrical%20Engineering%20from%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(BHU)%20Varanasi%20in%201989.%20After%20a%20brief%20stint%20at%20Wipro%2C%20he%20went%20to%20the%20US%20for%20an%20MBA%20at%20Northeastern%20University%20in%20Boston%2C%20Massachusetts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHis%20work%20journey%20started%20in%201992%20when%20he%20joined%20Fidelity%20Investments%2C%20where%20he%20took%20on%20roles%20in%20finance%20and%20technology%20management.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20became%20the%20Vice%20President%20of%20Fidelity%20Technologies.%20In%202000%2C%20he%20established%20T-Motion%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Deutsche%20Telekom%2C%20which%20later%20became%20part%20of%20T-Mobile's%20core%20services.%20He%20also%20served%20as%20the%20Chief%20Marketing%20Officer%20of%20the%20T-Mobile%20International%20Division%20of%20Deutsche%20Telekom%20AG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202004%2C%20Nikesh%20Arora%20joined%20Google.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalindian.com%2Fprofiles%2Fnikesh-arora%2F%C2%A0%5C%22%3Eheld%20major%20positions%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20Vice%20President%20of%20Europe%20operations%2C%20President%20of%20Europe%2C%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa%2C%20and%20ultimately%2C%20Senior%20Vice%20President%20and%20Chief%20Business%20Officer.%20He%20worked%20at%20Google%20for%20almost%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMr%20Arora%20then%20worked%20for%20Japan's%20SoftBank%20Corp%20in%202014.%20He%20became%20Vice%20Chairman%20of%20the%20group%20and%20CEO%20of%20SoftBank%20Internet%20and%20Media%20Inc.%20He%20was%20expected%20to%20succeed%20SoftBank's%20CEO%2C%20Masayoshi%20Son%2C%20and%20received%20%24208%20million%20in%20compensation%20over%20two%20years.%20However%2C%20in%20June%202016%2C%20he%20surprised%20everyone%20by%20resigning%20from%20his%20roles%20at%20SoftBank.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20join%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20in%202018%20and%20is%20now%20their%20CEO%20and%20Chairman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202015%2C%20Nikesh%20Arora%20was%20honoured%20with%20the%20Global%20Indian%20award%20at%20the%20ET%20Corporate%20Excellence%20Awards.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716368880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fllo4272g_nikesh-arora_625x300_22_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-nikesh-arora-indian-born-ceo-who-is-second-highest-paid-in-the-us-5719679%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nikesh%20Arora%20studied%20at%20The%20Air%20Force%20School%20before%20earning%20an%20Electrical%20Engineering%20degree%20from%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(BHU)%20Varanasi%20in%201989.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-nikesh-arora-indian-born-ceo-who-is-second-highest-paid-in-the-us-5719679%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-nikesh-arora-indian-born-ceo-who-is-second-highest-paid-in-the-us-5719679%