that%20if%20someone%20loses%20even%20one%20hour%20of%20sleep%2C%20it%20will%20take%20them%20days%20to%20recover.%20He%20also%20explained%20how%20sleep%20deprivation%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20range%20of%20symptoms%2C%20including%20headaches%2C%20poor%20focus%2C%20increased%20irritability%2C%20and%20even%20poor%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''If%20you%20lose%20just%20one%20hour%20of%20sleep%2C%20it%20could%20take%204%20days%20to%20recover%20from%20that.%C2%A0Sleep%20deprivation%20can%20cause%20various%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20headache%2C%20poor%20focus%20and%20attention%2C%20increased%20irritability%2C%20poor%20judgement%2C%20poor%20decision%20making%20and%20increased%20sleepiness%2C''%20Dr%20Kumar%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%20tweet%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EIf%20you%20lose%20just%20one%20hour%20of%20sleep%2C%20it%20could%20take%204%20days%20to%20recover%20from%20that.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSleep%20deprivation%20can%20cause%20various%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20headache%2C%20poor%20focus%20and%20attention%2C%20increased%20irritability%2C%20poor%20judgement%2C%20poor%20decision%20making%20and%20increased%20sleepiness.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2Fsleep%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23sleep%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FHealthyHabits%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23HealthyHabits%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Dr%20Sudhir%20Kumar%20MD%20DM%20(%40hyderabaddoctor)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhyderabaddoctor%2Fstatus%2F1792916538908893653%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMay%2021%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor's%20post%20has%20gone%20viral%2C%20with%20many%20users%20saying%20how%20sleep%20has%20become%20all%20the%20more%20vital%20than%20ever%20due%20to%20high-stress%20levels%20and%20poor%20lifestyle%20habits.%20The%20viral%20tweet%20also%20sparked%20widespread%20discussion%C2%A0about%20the%20critical%20importance%20of%20sleep%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20overall%20health%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20user%20asked%20him%20how%20many%20hours%20a%20person%20should%20sleep%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20break%20it%20down%20according%20to%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20average%20daily%20amount%20of%20sleep%20needed%2C%20by%20age%2C%20is%3A%20Newborns%20(up%20to%203%20months%20old)%3A%2014%20to%2017%20hours.%20Infants%20(4%20to%2012%20months%20old)%3A%2012%20to%2016%20hours%2C%20including%20naptime.%20Young%20children%20(1%20to%205%20years%20old)%3A%2010%20to%2014%20hours%2C%20including%20naptime.%20School-aged%20children%20(6%20to%2012%20years%20old)%3A%209%20to%2012%20hours.%20Teenagers%20(13%20to%2018%20years%20old)%3A%208%20to%2010%20hours.%20Adults%20(18%20years%20and%20up)%3A%207%20to%209%20hours.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20person%20enquired%20if%20the%20shortfall%20in%20hours%20of%20sleep%20can%20be%20compensated%20by%20sleeping%20in%20the%20daytime.%20Mr%20Kumar%20replied%2C%20''Absolutely.%20Sleeping%20for%207-9%20hours%20at%20night%20in%20one%20go%20is%20the%20best%20option.%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20can't%20get%20the%20entire%20quota%20of%20sleep%20at%20night%2C%20he%2Fshe%20could%20compensate%20the%20deficit%20in%20sleep%20by%20sleeping%20during%20daytime%20(second%20best%20option).''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20studies%20have%20shown%20the%20link%20between%20improper%20sleep%20and%20various%20disorders%20like%20weight%20gain%2C%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20decreased%20concentration%2C%20altered%20performance%2C%20and%20hormonal%20disorders%20amongst%20various%20others.%20It%20is%20linked%20to%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%20and%20mental%20disorders%